cian's%20assistant.%20I%20went%20to%20pre-med%20school%2C%20intending%20to%20become%20a%20surgeon.%20But%20now%20I%20work%20as%20an%20electrician.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20extremely%20rewarding.%20At%20the%20end%20of%20a%20job%2C%20you%20can%20turn%20the%20electricity%20on%20and%20see%20the%20whole%20system%20work%20right%20in%20front%20of%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20grew%20up%20around%20electricians.%20Several%20of%20my%20male%20family%20members%2C%20including%20my%20dad%2C%20are%20electricians.%20I%20did%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-i-didnt-go-college-university-apprenticeship-no-debt-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eapprenticeship%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20an%20electrician%20company%20in%202015%20and%20kept%20up%20electrician%20jobs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fside-hustle-pay-off-debt-passive-income-misconceptions-2024-04%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eon%20the%20side%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20I%20needed%20money%20for%20my%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'd%20work%20between%2020%20and%2025%20hours%20a%20week%20as%20an%20electrician.%20It%20was%20second%20nature%20to%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227df20752-f172-49cd-a922-2d381b6d6a76%5C%22%3EI%20wanted%20to%20become%20a%20surgeon%20but%20changed%20my%20mind%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20pre-med%20school%2C%20I%20chose%20to%20specialize%20in%20phlebotomy%20to%20get%20my%20foot%20in%20the%20door.%20But%20I%20had%20to%20work%20in%20a%20hospital%20drawing%20people's%20blood%20all%20day.%20I%20absolutely%20hated%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20thought%3A%20%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20a%20people%20person.%20I'm%20not%20meant%20to%20be%20here.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20at%20college%2C%20I%20got%20several%20personal%20trainer%20certifications%20and%20worked%20as%20a%20trainer%20on%20the%20side.%20But%20again%2C%20it%20didn't%20work%20for%20me.%20I'm%20good%20at%20speaking%20to%20people%2C%20but%20I'm%20quite%20antisocial.%20I%20like%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-side-hustles-for-introverts-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ework%20alone%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20kept%20up%20some%20electrical%20work%20on%20the%20side%2C%20too.%20I%20finished%20my%20degree%20with%20an%20associate's%20in%20pre-med%20in%202019%2C%20but%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquit-medicine-pivoted-corporate-job-better-work-life-balance-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EI%20decided%20not%20to%20continue%20in%20medicine%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b85fd89f-02dc-4446-9082-8802e9fedbe9%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20became%20a%20full-time%20electrician%20instead%20of%20continuing%20in%20medicine%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20could%20no%20longer%20work%20as%20a%20personal%20trainer%20under%20the%20COVID-19%20restrictions.%20Electricians%20were%20considered%20essential%20workers.%20I%20couldn't%20just%20stay%20unemployed.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-you-should-become-electrician-apprenticeship-job-growth-career-trend-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EI%20started%20working%20as%20an%20electrician%20full-time%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'd%20go%20on%20jobs%20solo%2C%20including%20running%20my%20own%20jobs%2C%20or%20with%20another%20person.%20Once%20the%20pandemic%20was%20over%2C%20I%20realized%20I%20wanted%20to%20keep%20doing%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228c58046d-3464-4e78-9111-74c6a10c7d64%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ENo%202%20days%20are%20the%20same%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20work%20a%2040-hour%20workweek.%20My%20shifts%20are%20normal%209-to-5%20working%20hours%2C%20but%20sometimes%20our%20hours%20change.%20We%20get%20told%20in%20advance%2C%20though.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20in%20an%20office%20job%20where%20you%20go%20to%20the%20same%20building%20every%20day%2C%20I%20work%20somewhere%20different%20every%20day.%20I%20experience%20different%20things%20and%20see%20different%20people%20every%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20a%20job%20is%20finished%2C%20I%20feel%20a%20sense%20of%20accomplishment%20and%20closure.%20I%20can%20finish%20the%20job%20and%20move%20on%20to%20another%20one.%20It%20doesn't%20feel%20like%20one%20long%20job%20forever.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e0091234-9877-4d9e-aef3-ba27b4389015%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThere%20are%20challenges%20and%20dangers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20gotten%20small%20electrical%20shocks%2C%20but%20that%20comes%20with%20the%20job.%20I've%20had%20an%20electric%20shock%20from%20an%20outlet%20before.%20That%20woke%20me%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarly%20in%20my%20career%2C%20I%20got%20a%20shock%20when%20I%20accidentally%20put%20my%20hand%20on%20a%20panel.%20Someone%20else%20had%20to%20pull%20me%20off%20the%20panel.%20I%20was%20slightly%20shaken%20after%20that%2C%20but%20it%20made%20me%20much%20more%20cautious.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20never%20been%20seriously%20injured.%20When%20working%20with%20more%20dangerous%20equipment%2C%20you%20wear%20more%20protective%20equipment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22216d16eb-7d6b-4cb5-a094-a28efa1847d2%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt's%20physically%20demanding%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20more%20experienced%20you%20get%2C%20the%20higher%20the%20voltage%20you%20can%20work%20with%20because%20you%20need%20to%20be%20experienced%20to%20work%20with%20deadly%20voltage.%20I%20mainly%20do%20commercial%20jobs%20now%2C%20such%20as%20pole%20lighting%20or%20utility%20generators%20for%20towns%20or%20businesses%2C%20though%20sometimes%20I%20still%20do%20residential%20work%20in%20people's%20homes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20prefer%20commercial%20work%2C%20but%20it%20can%20be%20tricky%20to%20troubleshoot%20and%20solve%20a%20problem%20when%20it's%20something%20I've%20never%20learned%20before.%20Moving%20heavy%20copper%20wire%20and%20big%20pipes%20can%20be%20labor-intensive%2C%20physical%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20to%20train%20in%20the%20gym%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20the%20men%20in%20the%20industry.%20Handling%20heavy%20equipment%20that%20is%20double%20my%20body%20weight%20can%20be%20more%20taxing%20on%20my%20body%20than%20theirs.%20There%20are%20days%20when%20I%20come%20home%20exhausted%2C%20but%20it's%20better%20than%20a%20repetitive%20office%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%225e340bf8-36ba-4636-be11-7915e2f03768%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI've%20experienced%20sexism%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20mostly%20work%20on%20my%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%2C%20when%20running%20jobs%2C%20I%20feel%20like%20people%20aren't%20taking%20me%20seriously.%20I%20haven't%20had%20many%20negative%20comments%2C%20but%20sometimes%2C%20I%20can%20tell%20from%20people's%20body%20language%20that%20they're%20uncomfortable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20worst%20was%20an%20older%20lady%20who%20asked%20my%20company%20if%20a%20male%20colleague%20could%20replace%20me.%20It%20used%20to%20upset%20me%2C%20but%20I%20don't%20take%20that%20stuff%20too%20seriously%20anymore.%20I%20know%20some%20people%20in%20the%20world%20just%20aren't%20used%20to%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20they%20see%20my%20work%2C%20there's%20no%20issue.%20Most%20people%20in%20the%20area%20of%20upstate%20New%20York%20I%20work%20in%20know%20me%20now%20anyway.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b6e8d36f-dbea-4520-bf14-02945ffecd6a%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI'm%20glad%20I%20became%20an%20electrician%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20glad%20I%20gave%20myself%20the%20opportunity%20to%20try%20other%20career%20paths%20to%20figure%20out%20they%20don't%20work%20for%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20happy%20where%20I%20am%20and%20excited%20to%20move%20into%20working%20with%20even%20higher%20voltage%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felectrician-switched-medicine-surgeon-degree-college-pre-med-gen-z-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715597348000%2C%22vis